---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
	title="About | Duojiang Field Notes"
	description="What this companion site is for and how it complements Duojiang's research website."
>
	<section class="about-hero surface-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
		<h1>A companion to the <a href="https://duojianghuji.github.io/duojiang-research-page/">research site</a></h1>
		<p class="lede">
			This site is for the material that benefits from slower looking: travel notes, micro photographs,
			reading traces, and short pieces that connect one place or image to another.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="detail-grid about-grid">
		<div class="meta-card">
			<h3>Why a second site</h3>
			<p>
				The research website stays concise and professional. This one can be more visual, more
				experimental, and more personal without making the scientific work harder to navigate.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="meta-card">
			<h3>What gets published here</h3>
			<p>
				Photo series, reading trails, place-based essays, short notes, and the kinds of observations that
				do not belong in a CV.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="meta-card">
			<h3>How to keep it alive</h3>
			<p>
				Add small entries regularly. Short, finished pieces are better than ambitious drafts that never
				reach the site.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
	.about-hero {
		padding: 1.75rem;
		border-radius: 0.45rem;
	}

	.about-grid {
		margin-top: 2.25rem;
	}
</style>
